description.2: The Power Pack and Franklin Richards work together to battle Jakal at the Statue of Liberty!
description.3: Luke and Leia return to Iskalon to tell Kiro's family of his death. Waiting for them... ruthless Nagai invaders. And Iskalon's staunchest defender is... Kiro himself!
description.4: He was Spider-Man's first "enemy". Now, years later, the story can finally be told. Whatever happened to Crusher Hogan?
description.5: The Avengers check out a hydro-base belonging to Sting-Ray, after the FAA prevents the team from launching Quinjets at the mansion. Namor shows up during the tour in a foul mood, but is in better spirits after a duel with Hercules. Cap offers Namor a spot on the Avengers roster, and the prickly king of Atlantis happily accepts! Namor's introductory issue as member of the Avengers!
description.6: Introducing: Flag-Smasher, the freedom-fighter gone mad! His goal: liberate Earth from the oppression of national rule! His target: The UN!
description.8: Confiscated by a group of scientists, the Hulk is now part of a dangerous experiment that can only end one way...
description.9: Scarlet Witch and Vizh travel to New Salem while discussing a family of their own. Salem's Seven assembles.
description.11: In his bid to become Earth's greatest hero, the One from Beyond may be embracing abject villainy. Guest-starring the Power Pack!
description.12: Stars are disappearing! As the Defenders float in space, Cloud shows them an empty vacuum that once hosted celestial bodies. Realizing that a being called Star-Thief is responsible, the Defenders kick off a mad dash to stop them!
description.13: He's New York City's Most Wanted Man -- and he has no clue why! After last issue's diamond heist, Longshot finds himself on the lam from the Amazing Spider-Man and She-Hulk!
description.17: Thor and his comrades ride into Hel! Upon arrival, Thor challenges Hela in combat. If he wins, the mortal souls trapped in Hel will go free, if Thor loses, he will be a servant to the goddess of the underworld forever!
description.19: The origin of Wonder Man and the Grim Reaper's childhood together is revealed! Can the remaining Avengers - along with The Vision and Scarlet Witch - save Wonder Man and Hank Pym before Ultron gets to them?
description.20: Doc Ock and one set of armored tentacles is bad enough, but when he's got two sets, and one of them is adamantium — what can Iron Man do?
description.21: Ultron and the Grim Reaper target Wonder Man's "brother," the Vision- and Scarlet Witch!
description.23: Beyonder develops the kind of depression only man can feel, and Earth's heroes must decide whether to strike. At his most vulnerable, will the nigh-omnipotent One succumb to Earth's mightiest? The Beyonder stares into the cosmic void, and the void stares back.
description.24: With the help of Seraph and the Defenders, Cloud searches through clues about their past!
description.25: Continued from SECRET WARS II #4. The Beyonder has Dazzler suspended over a shopping complex somewhere in Colorado -- and challenges her to put on the performance of her life.
description.26: Longshot gets involved in a civilian's dispute with Con Edison. And, after Longshot's memories of the Mojoverse are reignited, he's left with more questions than answers!
description.31: Firelord's flames can't be stoked! New York City will be razed if Spider-Man and the Avengers can't stop the former herald of Galactus. Peter Parker science whiz might just save the day.
description.32: The Avengers retreat from space following the aftermath of the battle between Nebula and the Skrulls. Cap contemplates the Beyonder's arrival to earth, and questions his motives.
description.33: Cap gets a new job - and wait'll you see what it is!
description.34: He's not just any dragon, he's Chiantang, brother of the Dragon King, the destroyer of K'un-Lun! And Iron Fist is not only going to fight, he's vowed to kill him!
description.35: The X-Men and Alpha Flight take the spotlight!
description.38: Who sits on the Deviants’ throne? A powerful ruler emerges, issuing a decree that the Eternals must forfeit their freedom to his Deviant subjects!
description.39: Han's relationship with Leia is on the rocks-and that's not all! Han's ready to leave-but more than just jumping ship, he's going to take off for a whole different universe! And because you demanded it: the return of Femm Syhsa!
description.40: Why is S.H.I.E.L.D. looking to bring in She-Hulk and what consequences will her capture have on Jennifer Walters?
description.46: Franklin Richards finds the Power children and tells them of his dream about Kofi and Jakal, and all kids set out to make sure the dream does not become reality.
description.47: The Sunturion is back and reducing people to ash! Can Daredevil beat the heat?!
description.48: When the Fantastic Four learn of some Skrull treachery, they navigate their way to the Skrulls base of operations. But what is the hyperwave bomb and is it too much for the FF? Guest-starring the Avengers!
description.49: Hulk meets Walter Langkowski, who tells our hero that he's looking for a body to rest his soul. But is it the Hulk's body Walter's referring to?
description.50: Tony Stark dons his ultimate state-of-the-art armor to beat Obadiah Stane! But will even his new armor be enough to defeat the man who's destroyed everything Stark holds dear?
description.51: The remaining New Mutants not under Karma's control are aided by Storm in launching their counterattack against their former ally.
description.54: A SECRET WARS II tie-in! The Beyonder is on Earth, and his havoc-wreaking comes knocking on the door of Alpha Flight! And to make matters worse, so does the one and only INCREDIBLE HULK!
description.55: It's an issue of full Femme Force as She-Hulk and the Invisible Woman triumph over Psycho-Man!
description.56: Professor X is dying?! Also, Rachel Summers unleashes the full fury of her powers!
description.59: Captain Britain encounters the most terrifying witch of Russian legend: Baba Yaga!
description.60: The adventures of one of the most beloved teams of Avengers start here! Wonder Man, Tigra and Iron Man investigate a robot attack, where they fall right into Ultron's trap! Can the heroes escape Ultron's clutches? And what is the mad A.I. REALLY after?
description.62: The Asgardians have returned! Thor heads out with Balder, the Executioner, and the Einherjar to Hel itself to free the mortal souls trapped there. Will they survive the dangers of the underworld?
description.64: Daredevil, blessed with the gift of sight! The otherworldly Beyonder restores what once was taken from Matt Murdock- why then is Matt begging to be blind again? And will the Beyonder hold up his end of the bargain?
description.65: The Triad reflects on Bruce Banner's life and realizes the important roles they've played throughout the years. Will these realizations help Bruce Banner become the Hulk's sole persona?
description.66: Tony Stark's friends are vanishing out of thin air. Is this the work of Obediah Stane?
description.67: Karma's betrayal of the New Mutants remains a mystery, one that Magik and Mirage are determined to unravel.
description.70: Our heroes are trapped in glass cylinders where the Psycho-Man continues to torture Sue Storm! Will the Invisible Woman unleash her rage against the villain? Meanwhile, where's She-Hulk?
description.71: A depowered Storm falls victim to elements. In her delirium, she is visited by her teammates. Will she find the strength necessary to live or will she give up and die?!
description.73: Can Captain Britain save his brother from the diabolical Dr. Crocodile? And more importantly, should he?
description.78: The Nagai invade the Alliance HQ on Endor! A computer has grounded the best Alliance pilots-Han and Luke-and Princess Leia must face the brunt of the attack alone!
description.79: You know Firelord! You've seen what he can do! Now his sights are on Spider-Man! The result? "Burn, Spider, Burn!"
description.80: The outer space battle rages on between the Avengers, Nebula, the Skrulls, and Thanos! The mysterious and twisted secret of Nebula revealed. How did the daughter of Thanos become the most merciless, ruthless woman in the galaxy?
description.81: In this issue: The Serpent Society is founded. Consisting of Sidewinder, Black Mamba, Death Adder, Princess Python, Cotton Mouth and Bush Master the venomous team targets Captain America and his comrades! Where's a snake charmer when you need one? Plus: An unexpected ally!
description.82: The mutant report continues with an inside look at Nightcrawler’s swashbuckling solo series!
description.83: Learn the origins of the Eternals and the Deviants in this inaugural issue from Marvel greats Peter Gillis, Sal Buscema, and Walt Simonson!
description.84: He's a synthetic man! She's a mutant sorceress! Once they were outcasts, but now they have each other, and a love which can withstand every danger they face! Steve Englehart and Richard Howell present...Vision and the Scarlet Witch!
description.86: The Beyonder has had his fill of superficial flings, craving the one thing that will make his mortal life complete- love! Enter Alison Blaire, the mutant songstress known as Dazzler. But will Beyonder realize the sacrifice love requires all too late?
description.87: Daimon and Patsy Hellstrom are tasked to find an occult statue called the Lesser Grey God!
description.88: Longshot's Hollywood debut! Marvel's luckiest mutant finds a dazzling partner in Ricochet Rita while doing stunt work on a film. But the demon Gog has very different plans for the duo!
description.89: Carmody sneaks up on Julie just as she is about to secretly enter Asgard! The Warriors Three guest-star!
description.93: Mary Jane struggles with her conscience over whether to reconcile with Peter. Spider-Man becomes a fire fighter after a building catches flame. But how are the people inside the building solid gold? Could this be the work of the Beyonder?
description.95: Iron Man vs. the tentacled wrath of Doc Ock! And Otto has some backup to boot!
description.97: The Beyonder indulges in all of Earth's pleasures, discovering quickly that humans can have too much of a good thing. His earthly education continues when Beyonder uncovers the secret of desire, turning all who meet him into loyal subjects!
description.98: The battle between the Defenders and Hotspur continues! Can the Defenders stop Hotspur's demonic illusions before it's too late?

0.text: Mr. Invisible is here and a certain amulet may mean big adventure!

7.text: Mother White is corrupting New York City with a drug ring, and Moon Knight must swing into action!

10.text: Secret Wars II tie-in! Ben Grimm connects the dots and starts to realize that the Beyonder may be responsible for his string of bad luck. In Brooklyn, the Beyonder kicks off a dangerous drinking binge…

15.text: Nightcrawler and Lockheed are sold into slavery…and are now the property of the sorcerer Shagreen! Captive in Shagreen’s tower, and his teleportation powers neutralized, how will Nightcrawler “bamf” his way out of this one?

16.text: The X-Men and Alpha Flight forces are scattered across the Arctic, as Loki continues his reign of confusion. Wolverine attacks two members of Alpha Flight. Heather Hudson and Professor Xavier attempt reconciliation. Rachel Summers goes missing. Mayhem and chaos abound, as the X-Men and Alpha Flight take on a common foe in the Elder Gods!

17.text: Thor and his comrades ride into Hel! Upon arrival, Thor challenges Hela in combat. If he wins, the mortal souls trapped in Hel will go free, if Thor loses, he will be a servant to the goddess of the underworld forever!

Thor and his comrades ride into Hel! Upon arrival, Thor challenges Hela in combat. If he wins, the mortal souls trapped in Hel will go free, if Thor loses, he will be a servant to the goddess of the underworld forever!

18.text: While away from Asgard, Balder's lord and master, the mighty Odin, perished. But for the gods, death is not the end... He'll have to join Thor for a journey in the underworld realm of Hel!

19.text: The origin of Wonder Man and the Grim Reaper's childhood together is revealed! Can the remaining Avengers - along with The Vision and Scarlet Witch - save Wonder Man and Hank Pym before Ultron gets to them?

20.text: Doc Ock and one set of armored tentacles is bad enough, but when he's got two sets, and one of them is adamantium — what can Iron Man do?

22.text: Gator versus the Thing! Ben Grimm has his work cut out for him when he faces a new foe in the ring.

27.text: Wicket Wystri Warrick & Teebo decide to take a shortcut home across the Valley of the Lizard Warriors after a long mission, but they are captured by an exiled Ewok, named Graak, and his Lizard Warriors. They are offered passage on the condition that they can survive a hunt in which they are the prey.

28.text: Marvel’s strangest mutant takes to the skies in his own mini-series! Kurt Wagner is more than the X-Man Nightcrawler - once a circus performer, Kurt still harbors dreams of swashbuckling adventure and derring-do. And those dreams may well become reality! While attempting to rescue Kitty Pryde’s dragon Lockheed, Nightcrawler is transported to an alien dimension of high-flying pirates, sorcery, and plenty of plundering!

29.text: Cyclops and Madelyne Pryor are transporting a group of Canadian scientists to the Arctic, when their plane is attacked by a mysterious force. Rachel Summers proposes an X-Men/Alpha Flight team-up, to save Cyclops, Madelyne, and the missing Canadians. The X-Men zip up their parkas as they head to the Canadian wilderness!

30.text: Guest-starring the Amazing Spider-Man! With the help of the Friendly Neighborhood crime fighter, Cloak and Dagger take down a crew of drug traffickers.

35.text: The X-Men and Alpha Flight take the spotlight!

36.text: Human Torch and the Thing star in “Strangers”! The Chief Examiner confronts the two heroes in order to save his home planet.

42.text: Spider-Ham 20,000 leagues under the sea…can pigs even swim?! Plus, Croctor Strange, Master of the Misfit Arts!

43.text: Planet Terry takes on a ‘hardcore’ identity in an alien penal colony! Time to enter…Alphatraz!

44.text: Lorna wants to be a princess but Roy shows her it's not all it appears to be.

52.text: As the Squadron Supreme take the next step of their Utopia Program, Doctor Spectrum begins to feel animosity towards Power Princess. What sort of internal conflict will this lead to? Plus, Nuke is missing and Spectrum is on his trail!

57.text: The Death of Jean DeWolff PART 2! Unhappy about the outcome of the trial, Spider-Man faces more trouble when the Sin-Eater opens fire in the courthouse and creates hysteria!

58.text: Who are the Worshippers of the White Cobra? And what do they want with Moon Knight!?

60.text: The adventures of one of the most beloved teams of Avengers start here! Wonder Man, Tigra and Iron Man investigate a robot attack, where they fall right into Ultron's trap! Can the heroes escape Ultron's clutches? And what is the mad A.I. REALLY after?

61.text: It’s the mother-daughter crusade you’ve been waiting for. Clea and Umar battle one-on-one, but whose powers are more superior? Only one will emerge triumphant and claim rulership of the Dark Dimension.

62.text: The Asgardians have returned! Thor heads out with Balder, the Executioner, and the Einherjar to Hel itself to free the mortal souls trapped there. Will they survive the dangers of the underworld?
The Asgardians have returned! Thor heads out with Balder, the Executioner, and the Einherjar to Hel itself to free the mortal souls trapped there. Will they survive the dangers of the underworld?

63.text: DARK GUARDIAN RISES! The resurrected hero reveals himself as a cybernetic saboteur, and takes Snowbird and Talisman hostage! How can Shaman make an impossible decision?

68.text: In "A Small Sacrifice," Tom Thumb will make a choice that will cast shockwaves through reality and irrevocably alter the fate of the world. Is it too late for the Squadron to act?

72.text: The Death of Jean DeWolff PART 1! Eager for justice, Spider-Man finds himself in court with Matt Murdock, also known as "Daredevil", during the trial for the gang attack on Mr. Popchik.

75.text: Terry teams up with Sam Space, intergalactic private eye, to take on a crustaceous calamity!

76.text: Can Top Dog stop a criminal from releasing 100 billion dollars in fake money?

82.text: The mutant report continues with an inside look at Nightcrawler’s swashbuckling solo series!

85.text: Will the Thing find success in his new career as a wrestler?

90.text: The piratical Bluebeard unleashes his villainy against Moon Knight and friends!

91.text: The Squadron Supreme is here! Prepare for a different kind of hero when the Squadron begins to rebuild society from the ground up! Is it better to be loved or feared? Will the Squadron's Utopia Program lead to peace or chaos?

92.text: Thor's Asgardian brethren have discovered Lorelei's love spell and attempt to break it. Now, Thor must confront Loki, for this scheme would have never been concocted if it were not for him. A battle between brothers ensues!

93.text: Mary Jane struggles with her conscience over whether to reconcile with Peter. Spider-Man becomes a fire fighter after a building catches flame. But how are the people inside the building solid gold? Could this be the work of the Beyonder?

94.text: Advantage: Omega Flight! Alpha Flight's dark rivals succeed in taking them down, and it seems that Guardian's recent resurrection has something to do with it. What dark secrets is he keeping from the rest of the team?

95.text: Iron Man vs. the tentacled wrath of Doc Ock! And Otto has some backup to boot!

96.text: Ben Grimm and Vance Astrovik vainly search for a woman who looks like Tarianna... but find the Thunderiders instead!

99.text: A bounty hunter with mutant killing gauntlets has his sights set on Alison!
